#. @info:tooltip Help text for RGB spinbox.
#: colordialog.cpp:197
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Red: 0⁠–⁠255</p><p>Green: 0⁠–⁠255</p><p>Blue: 0⁠–⁠255</p>"
msgstr "<p>წითელი: 0⁠–⁠255</p><p>მწვანე: 0⁠–⁠255</p><p>ლურჯი: 0⁠–⁠255</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for hexadecimal code.
#: colordialog.cpp:204
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hexadecimal color code, as used in HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: two-digit code "
"for red: 00⁠–⁠FF</p><p>GG: two-digit code for green: 00⁠–⁠FF</p><p>BB: two-digit "
"code for blue: 00⁠–⁠FF</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>ფერის თექვსმეტობითი კოდი, როგორც ეს HTML-ში გამოიყენება: #წწმმლლ</"
"p><p>წწ: ორციფრიანი კოდი წითლისთვის: 00⁠–⁠FF</p><p>მმ: ორციფრიანი კოდი "
"მწვანისთვის: 00⁠–⁠FF</p><p>ლლ: ორციფრიანი კოდი ლურჯისთვის: 00⁠–⁠FF</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSL (hue, saturation, lightness). Saturation: 0 means something on the grey axis; 255 means something between the grey axis and the most colorful color. This is different from “chroma” and should therefore get a different translation. Lightness: 0 means always black; 255 means always white. This is different from “brightness” and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:217
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>HSL-Saturation: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>Lightness: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>ტონი: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>HSL-გაჯერება: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>განათებულობა: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HWB (hue, whiteness, blackness). The idea behind is that the hue defines the pure (maximum colorful) color. Than, white color can be added, creating a “tint”. Or black color can be added, creating a “shade”. Or both can be added, creating a “tone“. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tint,_shade_and_tone for more information. 0% white + 0% black = pure color. 100% white + 0% black = white. 0% white + 100% black = black. 50% white + 50% black = gray. 50% white + 0% black = tint. 25% white + 25% black = tone. 0% white + 50% black = shade.
#: colordialog.cpp:231
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Hue: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>Whiteness: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>Blackness: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"
msgstr "<p>ტონი: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>სითეთრე: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>სიშავე: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSV/HSB. HSV (hue, saturation, value) and HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) are two different names for the very same color model. Saturation: 0 means something between black and white; 255 means something between black and the most colorful color. This is different from “chroma” and should therefore get a different translation. Brightness/value: 0 means always black; 255 means something between white and the most colorful color. This is different from “lightness” and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:244
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>HSV/HSB-Saturation: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>Brightness/Value: "
"0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>ტონი: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p><p>HSV/HSB-გაჯერებულობა: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>სიკაშკაშე/"
"მნიშვნელობა: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p>"

#. @label:slider Accessible name for lightness slider. This is different from “brightness”/“value” and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:255
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Lightness"
msgstr "სიკაშკაშე"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for CIELCH. “lightness” is different from “brightness”/“value” and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:260
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Lightness: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>Chroma: 0⁠–⁠%L1</p><p>Hue: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p>"
msgstr "<p>განათებულობა: 0%⁠–⁠100%</p><p>ქრომა: 0⁠–⁠%L1</p><p>ტონი: 0°⁠–⁠360°</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for Oklch. “lightness” is different from “brightness”/“value” and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:269
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Lightness: %L1⁠–⁠%L2</p><p>Chroma: %L3⁠–⁠%L4</p><p>Hue: 0°⁠–⁠360°</"
"p><p>Whitepoint: D65</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>განათებულობა: %L1⁠–⁠%L2</p><p>ქრომა: %L3⁠–⁠%L4</p><p>ტონი: 0°⁠–⁠360°</"
"p>><p>თეთრი წერტილი: D65</p>"

#. @label:slider An opacity of 0 means completely transparent. The higher the opacity value increases, the more opaque the colour becomes, until it finally becomes completely opaque at the highest possible opacity value.
#: colordialog.cpp:282
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Op&acity:"
msgstr "&გაუმჭვირვალობა:"

